title: Need help with this font...
content:
I'm hoping that this at least originated from a font, let me know if you have seen anything like this.

| Attachment | Size |
| --- | --- |
| [CentralCAInsul.jpg](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014194554/http:/typophile.com/files/CentralCAInsul.jpg) | 87.59 KB |
author: samuraixaq

comments.content: Highly unlikely: notice the differences is the lowercase a on the two lines. More likely, it’s hand-lettering: this particular style was popular in the 30s and 40s.

I'm afraid this is not a font, all repeating letters are different. BTW, I like [Kari](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014194554/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/kari) and [Mousse Script](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014194554/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/sudtipos/mousse-script).
Yeah, I kinda knew that, thank you for the help!
